BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC State African American Cultural Center
CATEGORIES:Lectures and Talks,Meetings and Conferences,Workshops and Traini
 ng,Community Events,Student Life
DESCRIPTION:Join the African American Cultural Center from 10 a.m. to  4 p.
 m. Feb. 19 for the Symposium on Afrofuturism and Diasporic Scholarship. A g
 raduate reception will begin at 5:30 p.m.\n\nThis year’s symposium theme\, 
 “We are the Architects\, We are the Future\,” invites participants to explo
 re the transformative power of Black radical imagination and the agency we 
 hold in shaping our own narratives. The symposium will provide vibrant spac
 es for future-making\, self-authorship and confidence-building. \n\nOur key
 note speaker\, David Washington\, an NC State alum and creator of the groun
 dbreaking graphic novel The Black Defender\, embodies this spirit of his vi
 sionary creation. His work models the power of belief\, representation and 
 writing ourselves boldly into the present and future. This year’s symposium
  celebrates the idea that we are not simply participants in tomorrow. We de
 sign the tomorrow we want to see. Through imagination\, scholarship and age
 ncy\, we affirm that we exist in the future\, and it will be a future that 
 we shape for ourselves. \n\nNC State students\, staff\, faculty and alumni 
 and community members and colleagues from the Triangle area are welcome to 
 attend.\n\nWe graciously thank our campus partners and financial sponsors f
 or helping to organize and support this event.
DTEND:20260220T000000Z
DTSTAMP:20260317T024530Z
DTSTART:20260219T150000Z
GEO:35.785108;-78.674529
LOCATION:Witherspoon Student Center\, African American Cultural Center
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Symposium on Afrofuturism and Diasporic Scholarship
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52072152130784
URL:https://calendar.ncsu.edu/event/symposium-on-afrofuturism-and-diasporic
 -scholarship
END:VEVENT
